         <div type="entry">
            <pb facs="https://leaf.bucknell.edu/sites/default/files/2026-01/diary71.jpg"/>
            <dateline>Wednesday 28.</dateline>
            <p>Warm, very warm. We received orders to move our camp across the Trent. The
               whole 22nd Division is to be encamped across there. We were nicely fixed here,
               but 2 months is a long time to have a fixed home here. We regret that we wonâ€™t
               have our quiet strolls into town, &amp; the prospect of wood ticks, mosquitos
               &amp; gnats is not agreeable. We received news from Beaufort that on last
               Thursday night Phillips had disappeared again and could not be found. He left
               his shoes in his room, &amp; got up a 12 oclock in the night in in the bath
               room. They suppose he is drowned but I am inclined to think he has wandered off
               again &amp; may turn up.</p>
         </div>
